<title>BRAZIL: Brazil Santos portworkers stop work over salary.</title>
<headline>Brazil Santos portworkers stop work over salary.</headline>
<dateline>RIO DE JANEIRO 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Portworkers in the public terminals at Brazil's port of Santos stopped work at 0700 local/1000 GMT in protest at a delay receiving their full April salary from the CODESP port authority, a port spokeswoman said.  </p>
<p>Because of a four-day strike by stevedores in April, CODESP has had cash flow problems and was only able to deposit 65 percent of portworkers' salaries yesterday, the spokeswoman said.</p>
<p>However, the 35 percent was expected to be deposited this morning, she added.</p>
<p>It was not clear whether portworkers would return to work when they received their full salary.</p>
